1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,400
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:04,400
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:08,840
My name is Catherine and we've got a very sad dialogue today actually, Marco.
我是Catherine，今天我们有一个非常悲伤的对话，Marco。

4
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:09,840
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:09,840 --> 00:00:15,240
Today we have a very sad but interesting dialogue of something that happens all the time.
今天我们有一个非常悲伤但有趣的对话，讲的是经常发生的事情。

6
00:00:15,240 --> 00:00:19,400
Maybe you have a girlfriend, maybe you had a boyfriend and you break up.
也许你有女朋友，也许你有男朋友，然后你们分手了。

7
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:23,180
That means you are no longer boyfriend and girlfriend.
这意味着你们不再是男女朋友了。

8
00:00:23,180 --> 00:00:26,780
Let's take a listen to today's dialogue and we'll be back in a moment to talk about what's
让我们听听今天的对话，稍后我们会回来讨论

9
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:27,780
going on.
发生了什么。

10
00:00:27,780 --> 00:00:32,780
Hello.
你好。

11
00:00:32,780 --> 00:00:38,780
Hey, do you want to go out tonight?
嘿，今晚想出去吗？

12
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:43,040
No, I think I'll pass.
不，我想我就不去了。

13
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:44,320
Mark broke up with me.
Mark和我分手了。

14
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:46,040
I feel awful.
我感觉糟透了。

15
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:47,040
What?
什么？

16
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:48,040
What happened?
发生什么事了？

17
00:00:48,040 --> 00:00:52,520
Just last week you were talking about going on vacation together.
就在上周你还在说一起去度假的事。

18
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:55,400
I don't know what I did wrong.
我不知道我做错了什么。

19
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:58,880
He said he needed some space to figure things out.
他说他需要一些空间来理清事情。

20
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:04,840
He said I didn't do anything wrong, that I'm a great person, just not the one for him.
他说我没做错什么，我是个好人，只是不适合他。

21
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:07,600
That's so cliche.
这太老套了。

22
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:10,080
Mark's not worth your time, Lydia.
Mark不值得你浪费时间，Lydia。

23
00:01:10,080 --> 00:01:12,560
You deserve so much better.
你值得更好的。

24
00:01:12,560 --> 00:01:17,600
I know we had hit a rough patch, but I had hoped we could work it out next weekend when
我知道我们遇到了困难，但我曾希望下周末

25
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:20,840
we both had some time off.
我们都有空时能解决。

26
00:01:20,840 --> 00:01:22,560
I think he found someone else.
我觉得他找了别人。

27
00:01:22,560 --> 00:01:26,520
I had been getting suspicious because he had been spending a lot of time with a co-worker.
我一直怀疑，因为他花了很多时间和一个同事在一起。

28
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:27,520
Whatever.
随便吧。

29
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,520
He's a jerk.
他是个混蛋。

30
00:01:28,520 --> 00:01:29,520
Forget about him.
忘了他吧。

31
00:01:29,520 --> 00:01:34,720
There are many more fish in the sea.
天涯何处无芳草。

32
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,000
Talk about being cliche, Maggie.
你还说我老套呢，Maggie。

33
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,680
But you're right.
但你说得对。

34
00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:41,720
There's no use for me to sulk around.
我闷闷不乐也没用。

35
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:43,720
Let's go out tonight.
我们今晚出去吧。

36
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:47,720
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

37
00:01:47,720 --> 00:01:50,920
So obviously this girl, Lydia, is very torn.
很明显，这个女孩Lydia非常伤心。

38
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:54,080
She's very sad because her boyfriend broke up with her.
她很难过，因为男朋友和她分手了。

39
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:55,080
That's right.
没错。

40
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:57,800
She's crying the whole time this dialogue was going on.
整个对话过程中她一直在哭。

41
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,240
That's right.
没错。

42
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:02,880
But she did mention, her and her friend mentioned some interesting things.
但她和她的朋友提到了一些有趣的事情。

43
00:02:02,880 --> 00:02:08,160
Why don't we take a look at some of the words they used on Language Takeaway.
我们来看看他们在“语言要点”中用到的一些词吧。

44
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:11,240
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

45
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:15,120
So first of all, her friend says, hey, do you want to go out tonight?
首先，她的朋友说，嘿，今晚想出去吗？

46
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,840
And what does Lydia say?
Lydia怎么回答的？

47
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:19,080
She says, no, I think I'll pass.
她说，不，我想我就不去了。

48
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,080
All right.
好的。

49
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:21,640
So she says, I think I'll pass.
所以她说，我想我就不去了。

50
00:02:21,640 --> 00:02:22,840
I will pass.
我就不去了。

51
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:25,520
So what does this verb mean, to pass?
那么这个动词“pass”是什么意思？

52
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:29,960
So that means she is politely rejecting the offer or the invitation.
意思是她礼貌地拒绝了提议或邀请。

53
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:30,960
So no thanks.
所以就是不了，谢谢。

54
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,960
No thanks.
不了，谢谢。

55
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:32,960
That's basically what it means.
基本上就是这个意思。

56
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:33,960
I won't go.
我不去。

57
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:36,760
So, hey, Marco, you want to go see a movie in a couple hours?
所以，嘿，Marco，你几个小时后想去看电影吗？

58
00:02:36,760 --> 00:02:38,040
No, I think I'll pass.
不，我想我就不去了。

59
00:02:38,040 --> 00:02:39,040
I got homework to do.
我有作业要做。

60
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,040
All right.
好的。

61
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,360
So Marco will not come.
所以Marco不会来。

62
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:44,400
That means to decline an invitation.
意思是拒绝邀请。

63
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:45,400
That's right.
没错。

64
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,200
So that's what it means to pass.
这就是“pass”的意思。

65
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:51,920
Now, as they continue to talk, they mention some of the problems with their boyfriend,
现在，他们继续聊，提到了和男朋友的一些问题，

66
00:02:51,920 --> 00:02:55,960
but Maggie said, ugh, that's so cliche.
但Maggie说，呃，这太老套了。

67
00:02:55,960 --> 00:03:01,120
So the boyfriend said something and Maggie thinks that what he said was very, very cliche.
所以男朋友说了些话，Maggie觉得他说得非常老套。

68
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,520
So what is something that is cliche?
那么什么是老套的东西？

69
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:09,120
Cliche means something that is said or done very often.
老套指的是经常说或做的事情。

70
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:11,560
It's almost like we would expect it.
几乎是我们预料之中的。

71
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:16,760
So like, for example, what's a cliche phrase or a cliche action?
比如，什么是老套的短语或行为？

72
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:20,520
Well, in the dialogue, they were talking about ways of breaking up with people.
在对话中，他们谈论的是分手的方式。

73
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:25,480
So for example, it's not you, it's me.
比如，不是你的问题，是我的问题。

74
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,480
Let's break up.
我们分手吧。

75
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:30,160
So that's a cliche because it's a sentence, it's a phrase everyone always says.
这很老套，因为这是一个句子，是每个人都会说的短语。

76
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:34,320
It's not very, maybe not very honest.
可能不太诚实。

77
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:40,320
Or like a movie cliche would be, you know, a couple, they're getting married, but their
或者像电影里的老套情节，比如一对情侣要结婚了，但

78
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:43,320
parents, the parents of the bride, they're divorced.
新娘的父母离婚了。

79
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,500
They hate each other.
他们互相讨厌。

80
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:47,720
But then at the wedding, they get back together.
但在婚礼上，他们又复合了。

81
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:49,320
They're going to get married again.
他们又要结婚了。

82
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,480
That's a cliche story.
那是个老套的故事。

83
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:52,480
That's right.
没错。

84
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:53,480
Because you've heard it before.
因为你以前听过。

85
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:54,480
Right.
对。

86
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,480
All the time.
总是这样。

87
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:56,480
It's very common.
这很常见。

88
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:59,480
So something that's very common, something that you would expect, that's almost, that's
所以，非常常见、你能预料到的事情，几乎就是——

89
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,480
a cliche.
老套。

90
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,920
And a cliche, calling something a cliche is not a good thing.
而说某件事老套，并不是什么好事。

91
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,960
It's usually a bad thing.
通常是个坏事。

92
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:04,960
That's right.
没错。

93
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:05,960
Okay.
好的。

94
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:11,440
So Maggie goes on to say that, you know, this guy, Mark, her ex-boyfriend, he's not really
所以玛吉接着说，你知道，这个家伙，马克，她的前男友，他其实——

95
00:04:11,440 --> 00:04:12,440
worth it.
不值得。

96
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:14,560
But she says, you deserve so much better.
但她说，你值得更好的。

97
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:15,560
Okay.
好的。

98
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:21,640
So to deserve is a verb and it means that you should receive something or you should
所以“deserve”是一个动词，意思是你应该得到某物或——

99
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:22,680
expect something.
期待某物。

100
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:27,280
So almost like, you know, in this case, you deserve better.
所以差不多就像，你知道，在这种情况下，你值得更好的。

101
00:04:27,280 --> 00:04:29,680
You have earned something better.
你赢得了更好的东西。

102
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,680
You're a good person.
你是个好人。

103
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:34,920
You should receive a, you know, you should have a good boyfriend.
你应该得到一个，你知道，你应该有一个好男朋友。

104
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:35,920
That's right.
没错。

105
00:04:35,920 --> 00:04:39,440
So when, when she says you deserve so much better, she's talking about deserving a better
所以当她说到“你值得更好的”时，她指的是值得一个更好的——

106
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,600
guy, a better man.
男人，一个更好的男人。

107
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:45,160
Or for example, so Marco, you work so hard at school.
或者举个例子，马可，你在学校那么努力。

108
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,340
You're always doing your homework.
你总是做作业。

109
00:04:46,340 --> 00:04:48,480
You really deserve good grades.
你真的值得好成绩。

110
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:51,360
It means you should receive good grades.
意思是你应该得到好成绩。

111
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:52,360
Very good.
非常好。

112
00:04:52,360 --> 00:04:54,840
Now, when Lydia said, yeah, you know what?
现在，当莉迪亚说，是啊，你知道吗？

113
00:04:54,840 --> 00:05:00,800
I just thought we were having some problems and we had hit a rough patch.
我只是觉得我们之间有些问题，我们遇到了困难时期。

114
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,660
So she's talking about a rough patch.
所以她提到了“rough patch”。

115
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:03,660
What is that?
那是什么？

116
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:07,760
A rough patch is actually something we talk about a lot in spoken English.
“Rough patch”实际上是我们口语中经常谈论的东西。

117
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:14,600
It's a way to describe a period of time, so maybe a week or a month when things are difficult,
它是一种描述一段时期的方式，可能是一周或一个月，当事情困难的时候，

118
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:20,040
you know, when maybe you argue with your boyfriend or girlfriend or when you're sad a lot or
你知道，也许你和男朋友或女朋友吵架，或者你经常伤心，或者——

119
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,240
when you're confused.
你感到困惑。

120
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:26,680
And so a period of time when you're angry or sad with your boyfriend or girlfriend,
所以一段你和男朋友或女朋友生气或伤心的时期，

121
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,760
that's a rough patch.
那就是“rough patch”。

122
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:32,040
So maybe we can apply a rough patch to another situation like at work.
所以我们也许可以把“rough patch”应用到其他情况，比如工作中。

123
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:34,120
Maybe you're going through a rough patch at work.
也许你正在经历工作中的困难时期。

124
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,360
That means I'm always busy.
那意味着我总是很忙。

125
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,400
I'm always tired.
我总是很累。

126
00:05:36,400 --> 00:05:37,960
I don't feel happy with my job.
我对工作不满意。

127
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,240
I'm going through a rough patch.
我正在经历困难时期。

128
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:44,400
So it's usually a temporary period of time where things are going bad.
所以这通常是一段暂时的、事情不顺利的时期。

129
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:45,400
It could be a week.
可能是一周。

130
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,400
It could be a month.
可能是一个月。

131
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,920
It could be a year.
可能是一年。

132
00:05:47,920 --> 00:05:50,160
But it's a fixed amount of time.
但这是一段固定的时间。

133
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,160
It's not forever.
不是永远。

134
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,160
It's just a period.
只是一段时期。

135
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:54,080
Okay, very good.
好的，非常好。

136
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:59,600
And Lydia went on to say that, you know, she thought that maybe he was going out with someone
莉迪亚接着说，你知道，她以为他可能和别人约会，

137
00:05:59,600 --> 00:06:06,600
else and she was suspicious because he was spending a lot of time with some other girl.
她很怀疑，因为他花了很多时间和另一个女孩在一起。

138
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:13,080
Okay, so to be suspicious is to think that something is happening, but you don't know.
好的，所以“suspicious”是认为某事正在发生，但你不知道。

139
00:06:13,080 --> 00:06:18,240
So for example, Marco, I think you've been taking the milk from the kitchen.
比如，马可，我觉得你一直在从厨房拿牛奶。

140
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:22,200
You are always drinking coffee and you always take milk in your coffee and there's no more
你总是喝咖啡，而且你总是在咖啡里加牛奶，现在没有——

141
00:06:22,200 --> 00:06:23,200
milk.
牛奶了。

142
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:24,200
So I think it was you.
所以我觉得是你。

143
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,540
I'm being suspicious.
我表示怀疑。

144
00:06:25,540 --> 00:06:28,480
I'm thinking that maybe you did something bad or wrong.
我在想也许你做了什么坏事或错事。

145
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,960
But I'm guilty.
但我有罪。

146
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:36,280
So maybe you're suspicious that someone is stealing the milk or maybe you suspect or
所以也许你怀疑有人在偷牛奶，或者你怀疑——

147
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:40,200
you're suspicious that your next door neighbor is maybe a car thief.
你怀疑你的邻居可能是个偷车贼。

148
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,200
Right.
对。

149
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,320
So you're very suspicious.
所以你非常怀疑。

150
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:46,200
That means you're always thinking that this person or someone else is doing something
那意味着你总是认为这个人或其他人正在做坏事——

151
00:06:46,200 --> 00:06:47,200
bad.
坏事。

152
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:48,200
That's right.
没错。

153
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:52,400
Okay, so a lot of words there talking about relationships, talking about cliches.
好的，所以这里有很多关于关系、关于老套的词语。

154
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:54,160
Why don't we go back?
我们为什么不回去呢？

155
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:59,760
Let's listen to the dialogue again and we'll be back in a bit with Fluency Builder.
让我们再听一遍对话，稍后我们会回来进行流利度训练。

156
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:01,760
Hello?
喂？

157
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:09,040
Hey, do you want to go out tonight?
嘿，你今晚想出去吗？

158
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:12,480
No, I think I'll pass.
不，我想我就不去了。

159
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,720
Mark broke up with me.
马克和我分手了。

160
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,360
I feel awful.
我感觉糟透了。

161
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:16,360
What?
什么？

162
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,360
What happened?
发生什么事了？

163
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:21,960
Just last week you were talking about going on vacation together.
就在上周你还在说一起去度假的事。

164
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:24,840
I don't know what I did wrong.
我不知道我做错了什么。

165
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:28,300
He said he needed some space to figure things out.
他说他需要一些空间来理清事情。

166
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:34,240
He said I didn't do anything wrong, that I'm a great person, just not the one for him.
他说我没做错任何事，我是个很好的人，只是不是他的那个人。

167
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,040
That's so cliche.
这也太老套了。

168
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,520
Mark's not worth your time, Lydia.
马克不值得你浪费时间，莉迪亚。

169
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:41,980
You deserve so much better.
你值得更好的。

170
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:47,040
I know we had hit a rough patch, but I had hoped we could work it out next weekend when
